column5: Blowing thru here now - power went out a couple times - super high winds, rain had visibility down to about 50 feet at best!  Be safe y'all!  Michael
it's a quick hitter.  the wall cloud at the front was impressive and tried awfully hard to rotate bringing lotsa people outside but thankfully just a light and sound show.
Nice pics can feel it comming this way
Where abouts are these pics ?   I'm heading up that way over night tonite - up to the French river by morning
brian will be barrie? storm should dissipate by 1am.

Might be another even larger band hit us yet - can't quite tell if it will just miss us or not.  I watched the last one cross lake st. john in about 90 seconds or so, rain got so intense I couldn't even see the shore in front of the house.  Michael
Coming through Woodbridge now, high winds and rain, shouldn't last long.
Getting really black here in ajax lightning to the north winds picking up
hit Jokeville at 8pm sharp!  my favorite part of a heat wave
Poor kid was killed here this morning .   A first year university of waterloo student walking in campus.   Stay safe everyone.
Im in Barrie Rich.  Safe travels.
skies just got real dark and wind is up and lots of thunder in Toronto now.
Thunder, lightning, big wind and heavy rain at 8:00 but now it seems like it may be winding down.  Best part is feeling the temps drop.
Picking up again in peterborough Lew . Should be your way in a minute.
Getting hammered here in Brighton...  G
I always watch the radar at Intellicast.com
Just tried that one woodenboater - much better composite than any I've seen yet!  Thanks!  Michael
